## Goal
Add helper methods to extract skills, commands, plugins, agents from profile directories using get-harness APIs.

## Dependencies
- Depends on: bridle-jm0 (Enhanced ProfileInfo data structures)

## Changes

Add extraction helpers (in src/config/manager.rs or new extractor module):

```rust
/// Extract resource summary from a DirectoryResource
fn extract_resource_summary(dir: &DirectoryResource) -> ResourceSummary {
    // List files in directory, return names
    // Handle directory not existing gracefully
}

impl ProfileManager {
    pub fn extract_skills(&self, harness: &Harness, scope: Scope) -> ResourceSummary {
        let dir = harness.skills(scope);
        extract_resource_summary(&dir)
    }

    pub fn extract_commands(&self, harness: &Harness, scope: Scope) -> ResourceSummary {
        let dir = harness.commands(scope);
        extract_resource_summary(&dir)
    }

    pub fn extract_plugins(&self, harness: &Harness, scope: Scope) -> Option<ResourceSummary> {
        // Only for OpenCode - returns None for other harnesses
        harness.plugins(scope).map(|dir| extract_resource_summary(&dir))
    }

    pub fn extract_agents(&self, harness: &Harness, scope: Scope) -> Option<ResourceSummary> {
        // Only for OpenCode - returns None for other harnesses
        harness.agents(scope).map(|dir| extract_resource_summary(&dir))
    }

    pub fn extract_rules_file(&self, harness: &Harness, scope: Scope) -> Option<PathBuf> {
        let rules = harness.rules(scope);
        if rules.exists { Some(rules.path) } else { None }
    }
}
```

## get-harness API Reference
- `harness.skills(scope)` -> DirectoryResource
- `harness.commands(scope)` -> DirectoryResource  
- `harness.plugins(scope)` -> Option<DirectoryResource> (OpenCode only)
- `harness.agents(scope)` -> Option<DirectoryResource> (OpenCode only)
- `harness.rules(scope)` -> DirectoryResource

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] extract_resource_summary helper implemented
- [ ] extract_skills() works for all harnesses
- [ ] extract_commands() works for all harnesses
- [ ] extract_plugins() returns Some for OpenCode, None for others
- [ ] extract_agents() returns Some for OpenCode, None for others
- [ ] extract_rules_file() returns path if rules file exists
- [ ] Graceful handling when directories don't exist
- [ ] cargo test passes
- [ ] cargo clippy passes

## Goal
Integrate all extraction methods to populate the enhanced ProfileInfo struct.

## Dependencies
- Depends on: bridle-jm0 (Enhanced ProfileInfo data structures)
- Depends on: bridle-jm1 (Directory resource extractors)
- Depends on: bridle-jm2 (Config extractors)

## Changes

Update ProfileManager::show_profile() in src/config/manager.rs:

```rust
pub fn show_profile(&self, harness: &Harness, profile_name: &str) -> Result<ProfileInfo> {
    let profile_path = self.get_profile_path(harness, profile_name)?;
    let mut extraction_errors = Vec::new();

    // Extract MCP servers with error capture
    let mcp_servers = match self.extract_mcp_servers(harness, Scope::Project) {
        Ok(servers) => servers,
        Err(e) => {
            extraction_errors.push(format!("MCP: {}", e));
            Vec::new()
        }
    };

    // Extract directory resources
    let skills = self.extract_skills(harness, Scope::Project);
    let commands = self.extract_commands(harness, Scope::Project);
    let plugins = self.extract_plugins(harness, Scope::Project);
    let agents = self.extract_agents(harness, Scope::Project);
    let rules_file = self.extract_rules_file(harness, Scope::Project);

    // Extract config values with error capture
    let theme = match self.extract_theme(harness, &profile_path) {
        Ok(t) => t,
        Err(e) => {
            extraction_errors.push(format!("Theme: {}", e));
            None
        }
    };

    let model = match self.extract_model(harness, &profile_path) {
        Ok(m) => m,
        Err(e) => {
            extraction_errors.push(format!("Model: {}", e));
            None
        }
    };

    Ok(ProfileInfo {
        name: profile_name.to_string(),
        harness_id: harness.kind().to_string(),
        is_active: self.is_active_profile(harness, profile_name)?,
        path: profile_path,
        mcp_servers,
        skills,
        commands,
        plugins,
        agents,
        rules_file,
        theme,
        model,
        extraction_errors,
    })
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] show_profile() populates all new ProfileInfo fields
- [ ] Extraction errors captured in extraction_errors vec
- [ ] Partial failures don't prevent returning ProfileInfo
- [ ] Works correctly for all three harnesses
- [ ] OpenCode-specific fields (plugins, agents, theme) populated
- [ ] Claude/Goose show None for unsupported fields
- [ ] cargo test passes
- [ ] cargo clippy passes

## Goal
Parse harness-specific config files to extract theme, model, and MCP server details with enabled status.

## Dependencies
